<concept id="concept_03A28F6BD0EA47DEAD4008F9EAF3C426">
  <title>Track Flash Content</title>
  <shortdesc>You can track links from flash buttons. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
    <p>Tracking Flash content enables you to track individual buttons, without
		requiring an mbox on the landing page. Tracking Flash content also lets you
		track interaction in the Flash content itself. For example, you might want to
		see how many different tabs a visitor clicks in the Flash element before
		clicking off the page. 
	 </p>
    <p>Make the following change to the Flash code to fire the mbox
		mbox-name-flashclick before transferring the visitor to the specified url: 
	 </p>
    <p>
      <table id="table_87A56FB2C592426B93C5221A4A83897C">
